REDIS_PASSWORD=your-redis-password

# ========================================
# DATABASE (if using separate database)
# ========================================
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/orbit_live

# ========================================
# SECURITY
# ========================================
# JWT Secret (for custom tokens)
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production

# Encryption key (for sensitive data)
ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-32-character-encryption-key

# ========================================
# CORS CONFIGURATION
# ========================================
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:5173,https://your-domain.com

# ========================================
# LOGGING
# ========================================
LOG_LEVEL=info

# ========================================
# FEATURE FLAGS
# ========================================
FEATURE_AI_ASSISTANT=true
FEATURE_REAL_TIME_COLLAB=true
FEATURE_FILE_UPLOAD=true
FEATURE_VIDEO_MEETINGS=false

# ========================================
# DEPLOYMENT
# ========================================
# Vercel, Netlify, etc. will set these automatically
# VERCEL=1
# VERCEL_URL=...
```

## üîí Security Notes:

### Client-Side Variables (VITE_*)
- These are exposed to the browser
- Safe to use: VITE_SUPABASE_URL, VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
- Never put secrets in VITE_* variables!

### Server-Side Variables
- Keep these secret!
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
- JWT_SECRET
- ENCRYPTION_KEY
- OAuth client secrets
- SMTP passwords

### Environment-Specific Files:
```
.env                  # Local development (gitignored)
.env.example          # Template (committed to git)
.env.local            # Local overrides (gitignored)
.env.development      # Development environment (gitignored)
.env.staging          # Staging environment (gitignored)
.env.production       # Production environment (gitignored)
```

## üìù Setup Instructions:

1. Copy this file:
   ```bash
   cp .env.example .env
   ```

2. Fill in your actual values in `.env`

3. Never commit `.env` to git!

4. For production, use:
   - GitHub Secrets (for CI/CD)
   - Vercel/Netlify Environment Variables
   - AWS Secrets Manager
   - HashiCorp Vault

## üß™ Verify Your Setup:

```bash
# Check if environment variables are loaded
npm run dev

# Should not show "Missing environment variables" error
```

